{
  "slug": "4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday",
  "title": "4 Islands of Eternal Spring for Your Perfect Holiday",
  "excerpt": "Leave behind the feeling of cold and changeable weather outside and make your plans to welcome the spring with a trip to the islands near Europe. Tenerife, Azores, Madeira and other islands of eternal spring are destinations where mild climate invite you to relax. Here’s what attractions await you in the seas off!",
  "content": "\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2><a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Madeira Archipelago, Portugal</a></h2>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Madeira, an autonomous region of Portugal, is an archipelago comprising 4 islands off the northwest coast of Africa. It is known for its namesake wine and warm, subtropical climate. The main island of Madeira is volcanic, green and rugged, with high cliffs, pebbly beaches and settlements on deltas of the Fajã River. Capital Funchal has botanic gardens and is known for its harbor and a large New Year’s fireworks show.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure class=\"wp-caption\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"388\" src=\"/images/posts/madeira-portugal-768x388.jpg\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-4369\" alt=\"Madeira Portugal\" srcset=\"/images/posts/madeira-portugal-768x388.jpg 768w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-300x152.jpg 300w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-1024x518.jpg 1024w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-320x162.jpg 320w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-640x324.jpg 640w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-360x182.jpg 360w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-720x364.jpg 720w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-1080x546.jpg 1080w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-800x405.jpg 800w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal-1280x647.jpg 1280w, /images/posts/madeira-portugal.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figcaption class=\"widget-image-caption wp-caption-text\"></figcaption>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The Greeks have given the name of “<a style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Islands of the Happy</a>” and, indeed, the climate of Madeira is a factor that can ensure happiness. The temperature during the early months of the year is 13-14 degrees Celsius and the green landscape invites you to walks in nature.&nbsp;<a style=\"background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Madeira</a>&nbsp;is a natural paradise with laurel forests and exotic plants, and in restaurants you can enjoy a fragrant wine produced on the island.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2><a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Azores Islands, Portugal</a></h2>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><a style=\"font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif; background-color: #ffffff;\" href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Azores Archipelago</a>&nbsp;carries the same distinctive note of eternal spring, being an ideal destination for those who want to escape for a few days of low winter temperatures.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sao Miguel Island</a>&nbsp;hosts some of the touristic attractions of the archipelago that are worth taking into account: botanical garden, volcanic landscape of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Lagoa de Foco</a>, dozens of waterfalls, and the largest city in the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Azores</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ponta Delgada</a>.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure class=\"wp-caption\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"380\" src=\"/images/posts/azores-768x380.jpg\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-4371\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"/images/posts/azores-768x380.jpg 768w, /images/posts/azores-300x148.jpg 300w, /images/posts/azores-1024x507.jpg 1024w, /images/posts/azores-320x158.jpg 320w, /images/posts/azores-640x317.jpg 640w, /images/posts/azores-360x178.jpg 360w, /images/posts/azores-720x356.jpg 720w, /images/posts/azores-1080x534.jpg 1080w, /images/posts/azores-800x396.jpg 800w, /images/posts/azores-1280x633.jpg 1280w, /images/posts/azores.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figcaption class=\"widget-image-caption wp-caption-text\"></figcaption>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The Azores, an autonomous region of Portugal, are an archipelago in the mid-Atlantic. The islands are characterized by dramatic landscapes, fishing villages, green pastures and hedgerows of blue hydrangeas. São Miguel, the largest, has lake-filled calderas and the Gorreana Tea Plantation. Pico is home to the 2,351m Mt. Pico and vineyards sheltered by boulders.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2><a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Tenerife, Spain</a></h2>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>The largest island of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Canary Islands</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Tenerife</a>, has in January an average temperature of 16 degrees. This aspect is speculated most of the tourists who want to enjoy the beautiful weather of spring and walks outdoors. Moreover, prices are more than affordable in this period.</p><p>&nbsp;</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure class=\"wp-caption\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"512\" src=\"/images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-768x512.jpg\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-4392\" alt=\"Loro Park Tenerife Spain\" srcset=\"/images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-768x512.jpg 768w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-300x200.jpg 300w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-1024x682.jpg 1024w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-320x213.jpg 320w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-640x427.jpg 640w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-360x240.jpg 360w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-720x480.jpg 720w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-1080x720.jpg 1080w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain-800x533.jpg 800w, /images/posts/loro-park-tenerife-canary-islands-spain.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figcaption class=\"widget-image-caption wp-caption-text\">Loro Park -- Tenerife, Spain | Image by Luís Gonçalves from Pixabay </figcaption>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><span style=\"color: var( --e-global-color-text ); font-family: var( --e-global-typography-text-font-family ), Sans-serif;\">The island hides a lot of points less known by tourists. <a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Loro Natural Park</a>, with its orchids garden and an exceptional zoo is such a place. You can also visit the mysterious pyramids Guimar, which are similar to those in Mexico, Peru and Mesopotamia, and in the south of the island, Barranco del Infierno gorge you will impress you with its lush vegetation.</span></p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure class=\"wp-caption\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"423\" src=\"/images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-768x423.jpg\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-4387\" alt=\"Tenerife\" srcset=\"/images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-768x423.jpg 768w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-300x165.jpg 300w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-1024x564.jpg 1024w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-320x176.jpg 320w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-640x353.jpg 640w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-360x198.jpg 360w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-720x397.jpg 720w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-1080x595.jpg 1080w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-800x441.jpg 800w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands-1280x706.jpg 1280w, /images/posts/tenerife-canary-islands.jpg 1366w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figcaption class=\"widget-image-caption wp-caption-text\"></figcaption>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Tenerife</a> is the largest of Spain’s <a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Canary Islands</a>, off West Africa. It’s dominated by Mt. Teide, a dormant volcano that is Spain’s tallest peak. Tenerife may be best known for its <a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Carnaval de Santa Cruz</a>, a huge pre-Lent festival with parades, music, dancing and colorful costumes.</p><p>The island has many beaches (with sands from yellow to black) and resort areas, including Los Cristianos and Playa de las Américas.</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2><a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Ischia, Italy</a></h2>\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\nThe Italian island off the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bay of Naples</a>&nbsp;is perfect for tourists in search of spring. The temperature reaches 15 degrees, and hot springs await you at every step. Unmissable sights: thermal park Aphrodite and Apollo,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Aragonese Castle</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Malcovati Palace</a>.\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figure class=\"wp-caption\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"768\" height=\"499\" src=\"/images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-768x499.jpg\" class=\"attachment-medium_large size-medium_large wp-image-1452\" alt=\"Aragonese Castle Ischia, Italy\" srcset=\"/images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-768x499.jpg 768w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-300x195.jpg 300w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-1024x666.jpg 1024w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-320x208.jpg 320w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-640x416.jpg 640w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-360x234.jpg 360w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-720x468.jpg 720w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-1080x702.jpg 1080w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia-800x520.jpg 800w, /images/posts/Aragonese-Castle-Ischia.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\">\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<figcaption class=\"widget-image-caption wp-caption-text\">Ischia, Italy | <span style=\"font-size: 85%;font-weight:300\">Image Credits: <a>Otrebor81~commonswiki</a></span></figcaption>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</figure>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Ischia is a volcanic island in the Gulf of Naples, Italy. It’s known for its mineral-rich thermal waters. Hot springs bubble up at Maronti Beach, in the south. East, Roman remains lie beneath the sea floor at <a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Cartaromana Beach</a>.</p><p>The beach has views of medieval <a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Aragonese Castle</a>, linked to <a href=\"https://travelplaninfo.com/4-islands-of-eternal-spring-for-your-perfect-holiday/\">Ischia</a> by a stone bridge. Nearby, 18th-century Palazzo dell’Orologio houses the Sea Museum, devoted to Ischia’s fishing tradition</p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\n\t\t",
